 </office:master-styles>
 <office:body>
  <office:text text:use-soft-page-breaks="true">
   <text:sequence-decls>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Illustration"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Table"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Text"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Drawing"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Figure"/>
   </text:sequence-decls>
   <text:h text:style-name="P3" text:outline-level="2">Introduction</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5">The goal of the system is to unobtrusively monitor customer loyalty without requiring the customer to carry identification cards, especially in Japan where many small purchases are made in cash.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5">It will consist of two compoments: (1) A smart network camera with CIRC-CO facial recogniton embedded. (2) A <text:span text:style-name="T1">touch-sensitive </text:span>display monitor at the cash register showing the customers and their recent prevoius visits. Optionally the system can <text:span text:style-name="T1">be networked with other sister stores in the area.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="P3" text:outline-level="2">Revinue</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="P6">Revinue can be generated from: (1) Initial hardware cost, less then <text:span text:style-name="T3">¥80,000. (2) Hardware service maintenance contract, approximately ¥16,000 per month. (3) Optional inter-store networking connection one-time setup, ¥16,000 (existing WiFi) or ¥40,000 (new). (4) Optional Internet Database connection, ¥16,000 per month, (5) Optional new Internet connection, ¥16,000 per month.</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P6"><text:span text:style-name="T3"/></text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="P3" text:outline-level="2">Hardware</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="P6"><text:span text:style-name="T3"/></text:p>
